The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili STUDENTS at Hillside Teachers’ College in Bulawayo this morning staged a peaceful demonstration at the institution premises protesting a $300 boarding fees top up. The students alleged that they were paying $175 before the college hiked their fees to $475. They said the college on Tuesday demanded that they commit to paying the boarding fee increment by tomorrow  or risk being ejected from the institution’s hostels on Saturday. More details to follow. . .